    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1006"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 853.00/198.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Portugal</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Portugal</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1911</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the National
                    Constituent Assembly met yesterday at Lisbon and adopted the republican form of
                    government for Portugal.</p>
                <p>In making this communication to your excellency, I am directed to assure the
                    Government and people of the United States of America of the cordial friendship
                    and good-will of the Government and people of Portugal and to express their
                    earnest hope that the new order of things may prove a factor in drawing the two
                    countries together in closer association, to the lasting benefit of their mutual
                    interests.</p>
                <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alte.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
